Question 1) 
Write a Java program to get a number from the user and print whether it is positive or negative.

Answer:

import java.util.*;
public class Basics{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("Please write a number");
        int number = sc.nextInt();
        if(number>0)
        {
            System.out.println("Number is Positive");
        }
        else if(number<0)
        {
            System.out.println("Number is Negative");
        }
        else
        {
            System.out.println("0 is a Neutral Number");
        }
    }
}

Question 2)
Finish the following code so that it prints you hava a fever if your temperature is above 100 
and otherwise prints you dont have a fever.

public class Solution{
  public static void main(String args[]){
  double temp = 103.5;
  }
}

Answer:-

import java.util.*;
public class Basics{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        double temp = 103.5;
        if(temp>100)
        {
            System.out.println("You have a fever");
        }
        else
        {
            System.out.println("You dont have a fever");
        }
    }
}

Question 3)
Write a Java Program to input week number(1-7) and print day of week name using switch case.

Answer:-
import java.util.*;
public class Basics{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("Enter week number from 1-7");
        int weeknumber = sc.nextInt();
        switch(weeknumber)
        {
            case 1 :
                {
                    System.out.println("Monday");
                           break;
                }
            case 2 :
                {
                    System.out.println("Tuesday");
                           break;
                }
            case 3 :
                {
                    System.out.println("Wednesday");
                           break;
                }
            case 4 :
                {
                    System.out.println("Thursday");
                           break;
                }
            case 5 :
                {
                    System.out.println("Friday");
                           break;
                }
            case 6 :
                {
                    System.out.println("Sturday");
                           break;
                }
            case 7:
                {
                    System.out.println("Sunday");
                           break;
                }
            default:
                {
                    System.out.println("Invalid,Please write a valid week number");
                }
        }
        }
    }


Question 4)
What will be the value of x & y in the following program:

public class Solution{
public static void main(String args[]){
int a = 63, b = 36;
boolean x = (a<b)? true:false;
int y = (a>b)? a:b;
 }
}


Answe:- value of x = false     value of y = y=a=63

Question 5)
Write a java program that takes a year from the user and print whether that year is a leap year or not.

hint:
1)Year Divisible by 4 -Leap year (if not then not a leap year)
2) Year Divisible by 400 -Leap year(If not then not a leap year
3)Year Not divisible by 100 - Leap year( if yes then not a leap year)

LEAP YEAR- a year which has 366 days(The extra day is the 29th februrary, there is a leap year every four years).

Answer:


import java.util.*;
    public class Basics{
        public static void main(String args[]){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
            System.out.println("Enter a year");
            int year = sc.nextInt();
            if(year%4 == 0)
            {
            if(year%100 == 0)
            {
                    if(year%400 == 0)
                    {
                    System.out.println("LEAP YEAR");
                    }
                    else
                     {
                System.out.println("Not Leap year");
                     }
            }
            else
            {
                 System.out.println(" Leap year");
            }
            }
            else
            {
                 System.out.println("Not Leap year");
            }
        }
    }




